What does our body language tell others, about us?

1
00:00:09,420 --> 00:00:14,280
It was quite popular, particularly, in the 1970’s and 1980’s for people to write

2
00:00:14,280 --> 00:00:16,270
books about body language.

3
00:00:16,270 --> 00:00:20,340
These books promised that if you could learn the secrets of body language, you&#39;d be able

4
00:00:20,340 --> 00:00:25,149
to effectively read people&#39;s minds, to know what they were thinking if they crossed their

5
00:00:25,149 --> 00:00:28,800
arms, or scratched their nose, or looked to the left.

6
00:00:28,800 --> 00:00:32,680
Maybe you could even convince them to like you more through adjusting your own body language.

7
00:00:32,680 --> 00:00:36,730
For the most part, these claims are massively overstated.

8
00:00:36,730 --> 00:00:40,640
Despite what your friends think, when you study psychology you aren’t going to learn

9
00:00:40,640 --> 00:00:43,020
how to read people&#39;s minds.

10
00:00:43,020 --> 00:00:47,660
Having said that, nonverbal communication is a major avenue through which we reach other

11
00:00:47,660 --> 00:00:48,660
people.

12
00:00:48,660 --> 00:00:52,180
It&#39;s a major avenue through which we miscommunicate, as well.

13
