18
00:01:15,190 --> 00:01:18,860
So, what do we mean by nonverbal communication?

19
00:01:18,860 --> 00:01:21,430
It&#39;s a much broader definition than many people imagine.

20
00:01:21,430 --> 00:01:24,720
It’s effectively anything other than the words.

21
00:01:24,720 --> 00:01:28,810
Obviously, this includes things like hand gestures, and facial expressions.

22
00:01:28,810 --> 00:01:33,690
It can also include things like your voice, whether you&#39;ve got a high-pitched voice or

23
00:01:33,690 --> 00:01:34,690
a loud voice.

24
00:01:34,690 --> 00:01:40,990
It can include posture, touch, clothes, a whole range of things actually.

25
00:01:40,990 --> 00:01:46,380
There&#39;s nothing in the definition that suggests that nonverbal communication has to be intentional.

26
00:01:46,380 --> 00:01:50,710
When you put clothes on this morning, presumably you were not necessarily trying to send the

27
00:01:50,710 --> 00:01:54,990
message to the world about how you&#39;re feeling, or the kind of person that you are, but some

28
00:01:54,990 --> 00:01:59,060
people might make those assumptions about you in any case.

29
00:01:59,060 --> 00:02:03,670
According to the definition, communication has happened with or without your permission,

30
00:02:03,670 --> 00:02:05,660
with or without your intention.

31
00:02:05,660 --> 00:02:09,380
There&#39;s nothing in the definition that suggests that it has to be accurate.

32
00:02:09,380 --> 00:02:13,980
People can make all sorts of mistaken assumptions on the basis of your body language, your clothes,

33
00:02:13,980 --> 00:02:16,670
whatever it is, but that&#39;s still nonverbal communication.

